For 3 short ribs, 1kg incl. bone

[ rub ]
- 20g (1 tbsp) brown sugar (sub white)
- 5g (2 tsp) paprika
- 2.5g (1 tsp) garlic powder (sub 1 tsp fresh garlic)
- 1.5g (1 tsp) onion powder (sub garlic powder)
- 0.5 tsp cumin powder
- 2.5g (0.75 tsp) mustard powder (Note 2)
- 1 tsp cooking salt / kosher salt (reduce by 25% for table salt, increase 50% for salt flakes)
- 0.5g (0.5 tsp) black pepper

[ sauce ]
- 2 garlic cloves , minced (sub 2 tsp powder)
- 125 ml apple cider vinegar (Note 2 subs)
- 335 g ketchup , or Aussie tomato sauce
- 80 g brown sugar , loosely packed (ie don't pack it tight)(sub white)
- 2 tsp EACH black pepper, onion powder, mustard powder (Note 2)
- 1 tsp cayenne pepper (adjust to taste re: spiciness)
- 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce (sub soy sauce)
- 500 ml water

[ procedure - slow-cooker ]
- replace oven with slow cooker
- reduce sauce to replace oven evaporation

[ procedure - oven ]
- oven to 160°C
- coat ribs in rub
- make sauce (except water) in baking pan, then add water
- coat ribs in sauce
- bake meat side down 3.5hr covered with lid or foil until meat pulls apart
  - baste intermittently
- spoon sauce over then separate meat and strain sauce
- finish over barbecue, basting regularly

